	   <tr><td colspan=2>Lothaine/Shassix and Herricane, this is especially for you, but others too, I'm sure:<br><br>It seems that we have given some information about Monk damage-bonusses that has been misunderstood, so I will try to clarify this.<br><br>Keyeluke and myself have been preaching that you should put the low-delay weapon in your primary hand to take full advantage of the bonusses monks get. HOWEVER, since the bonus is (Level-25)/3 rounded down (And only applies to your primary hand), the low delay-tactic isn't usefull until well in to your thirties (you don't even get the first bonus-damage point until lvl 28).<br><br>Shassix, at Lvl 15 you are using a Wu Stick in your primary hand, leaving the KD in your secondary - But until lvl 35 or so, when you have a nice bonus and the Wu procs, the KD is a VASTLY better weapon, and a Wu Stick is outclassed even by a basic Fighting Baton! You should put the Wu Stck back in the bank and look for a FB or CoT for your secondary and have your KD in the Primary for maximum damage-output.<br><br>Herricane, it's the same basic deal (You're 20th or so, right?): You have your better, but slower weapon (CoT) in you secondary and a FB in the primary. Switch these two, and switch back again around lvl 35-36 to maximise your ability to kick butt.<br><br>Both you guys have excellent weapon setups (Especially Shassix...Wow), but you are getting a bit ahead of yourselves.<br><br>I hope this was clear enough, otherwise please ask. (And Keyeluke, I hope I got this right...)<br>&nbsp;<br>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar Monk<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115679" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115679</a></td></tr>
